data.name: Cheesy Baked Cauliflower Casserole
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and cheesy delight that makes cauliflower irresistible!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the cauliflower into florets and steam or boil until tender, about 5 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, cheddar cheese, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, milk, salt, and pepper. Mix until smooth.
Add the cooked cauliflower to the cheese mixture and stir until well coated.
Transfer the mixture into a greased baking dish. Dot the top with butter.
Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes until the top is golden and bubbly.
